      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:2c0efcfbe2283edc",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 201,
        "char_start": 171,
        "episode_id": "e1743bda-76ff-5586-9e39-3fa45e41ef9a",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Thanks, Leo. Great to be back.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 12000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 6000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:5d969c77fe7d914a",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 356,
        "char_start": 207,
        "episode_id": "e1743bda-76ff-5586-9e39-3fa45e41ef9a",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Today's episode is sponsored by Adobe. Adobe Creative Cloud puts Lightroom, Photoshop, and Premiere on every device you edit on. Try adobe.com today.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:6072fed2effee292",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 465,
        "char_start": 356,
        "episode_id": "e1743bda-76ff-5586-9e39-3fa45e41ef9a",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "How do you know when you've gotten it right? What's the structural angle most listeners don't have access to?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:1e033119a44b5717",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 714,
        "char_start": 473,
        "episode_id": "e1743bda-76ff-5586-9e39-3fa45e41ef9a",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Here's how I think about it. On location, the first decision is always: am I shaping the existing light, or building from scratch? We've seen this play out at teams using Capture One. And the second-order effect is the part most people miss.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:51e4e2eedd0ee18f",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 797,
        "char_start": 720,
        "episode_id": "e1743bda-76ff-5586-9e39-3fa45e41ef9a",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "What does that look like day-to-day? How does frame change the calculus here?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
